    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix missing null terminator on APN string buffer causing out-of-bounds read\n\n### Summary\nThe ESM layer contained a bug where OctetString data (specifically APN values) was being used directly in logging functions without ensuring null termination. This led to out-of-bounds reads when string functions tried to process the non-null-terminated data.\n\nThe issue was introduced when the code was refactored to use OctetString structures for APN handling but the logging code wasn't updated to handle the non-null-terminated nature of these buffers.\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder certain network conditions when processing PDN connectivity accept messages with specific APN values, the gNB would crash with a segmentation fault in the logging subsystem. The crash occurred when trying to print APN information in ESM procedure logs.\n\nThe issue was most reproducible when:\n1. UE attempts PDN connectivity with a non-printable first byte in APN\n2. Logging level is set to INFO or higher\n3. Multiple PDN connections are established simultaneously\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/UE/ESM/PdnConnectivity.c`: Added null-terminated copy of APN data for safe string operations in logging functions\n- Fixed all instances where `apn->value` was used directly as string in `LOG_TRACE` calls\n- Added proper bounds checking to prevent buffer overflows\n\n"
}